alert.note: Alert for Coastal Franklin; Coastal Gulf (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Wind Advisory issued April 12 at 11:34PM EDT until April 13 at 6:00AM EDT by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM EDT /5 AM CDT/ THURSDAY... * WHAT...East winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph. * WHERE...Coastal Gulf and Coastal Franklin Counties. * WHEN...Until 6 AM EDT /5 AM CDT/ Thursday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong east winds will be strongest along the coast of Franklin County, including the Big Bend Scenic Byway, and over coastal Gulf County south of Port Saint Joe.
info.instruction: A Wind Advisory means that sustained winds of 26 to 39 mph are expected for at least 2 hours, or gusts between 40 to 57 mph for any length of time are possible.Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profilevehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
